
Function: EVENP

Syntax:   (EVENP arg1)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - an integer.

Returns:

 T if arg1 is even (divisible by two), else NIL.

Processing:

Errors signaled:

 Non-integer argument.

Notes:

 No errors are detected in compiled code; results are unpredictable
 if an invalid argument is passed.

Examples:

 (EVENP 0)        ==> T
 (EVENP 7)        ==> NIL
 (EVENP -8)       ==> T

